texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: · Research Focus: This thesis investigates the design and simulation of a Dual Active Bridge (DAB) -based Partial Power Processing converter (PPPC) architecture for electric vehicle (EV) chargers, aiming to enhance efficiency and reduce overall system size under the supervision of Prof. Amarendra Edpuganti.
texts.text: Research Focus: This thesis investigates the design and simulation of a Dual Active Bridge (DAB) -based Partial Power Processing converter (PPPC) architecture for electric vehicle (EV) chargers, aiming to enhance efficiency and reduce overall system size under the supervision of Prof. Amarendra Edpuganti.

texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: · Scope: The study involves theoretical analysis and extensive simulation to optimize the PPPC architecture design, control strategies and component selection, emphasizing the practical application in fast-charging systems .
